# Color & Contrast üé®

Ensure content is readable by everyone.

## Contrast Ratios:
| Level | Normal Text | Large Text |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| AA | 4.5:1 | 3:1 |
| AAA | 7:1 | 4.5:1 |

## Examples:
```css
/* ‚ùå Low contrast */
.bad {
    color: #666;
    background: #888;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good contrast */
.good {
    color: #000;
    background: #fff;
}
```

## Don't Rely on Color Alone:
```html
<!-- ‚ùå Color only -->
<span style="color: red;">Error</span>

<!-- ‚úÖ Color + icon + text -->
<span style="color: red;">‚ö†Ô∏è Error: Invalid email</span>
```

## Tools:
- WebAIM Contrast Checker
- Chrome DevTools contrast
- Lighthouse audit

# Skip Links ‚è≠Ô∏è

Allow keyboard users to skip repetitive content.

## Implementation:
```html
<body>
    <a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">
        Skip to main content
    </a>
    <header>...</header>
    <nav>...</nav>
    <main id="main-content" tabindex="-1">
        <!-- Main content -->
    </main>
</body>
```

## CSS:
```css
.skip-link {
    position: absolute;
    top: -40px;
    left: 0;
    padding: 8px;
    background: #000;
    color: #fff;
    z-index: 100;
}

.skip-link:focus {
    top: 0;
}
```

## Benefits:
- Skip navigation on every page
- Jump to content quickly
- Essential for keyboard users
- Visible only when focused

# Common A11y Mistakes ‚ùå

## 1. Removing Focus Outlines:
```css
/* ‚ùå Never */
:focus { outline: none; }

/* ‚úÖ Replace with custom */
:focus {
    outline: 2px solid blue;
}
```

## 2. Using `<div>` as Buttons:
```html
<!-- ‚ùå Not keyboard accessible -->
<div onclick="submit()">Submit</div>

<!-- ‚úÖ Proper button -->
<button onclick="submit()">Submit</button>
```

## 3. Missing Form Labels:
```html
<!-- ‚ùå Placeholder is not a label -->
<input placeholder="Email">

<!-- ‚úÖ Proper label -->
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input id="email">
```

## 4. Low Contrast:
```css
/* ‚ùå Hard to read */
.text { color: #999; background: #ddd; }

/* ‚úÖ Sufficient contrast */
.text { color: #333; background: #fff; }
```
